&lt;suggest&gt;Old Commodore Monitor&lt;/suggest&gt;<br /><br />Levity aside, as interesting as it might be to modify the PowerPak menus, I agree that the gameplay will suffer as well and you should look into getting a different display.<br /><br />-Xious<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />My cousin has to use his NES and PowerPak with a half-broken TV. Each scanline is offset to the right by a random distance, much like the "fuzz out" in the second dose of <a href="http://www.pineight.com/tod/" class="postlink">Lockjaw: The Overdose</a>. The more black in the image, the more ragged the horizontal sync is. Depending on the amount of black, this could range from a 2-pixel range to an 8-pixel range. And guess how much black is in the PowerPak menu system.<br /><br />So would it be feasible to edit the PowerPak menu? He wants to do the following:<br /><ul><li>Turn on the monochrome bit or otherwise set the background to $00 gray (not $0F black) </li><li>Change the font to make the letters used in Game Genie codes more distinctive </li></ul><br /></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> — Thu Mar 04, 2010 2:43 am</p><hr />
