<title type="html"><![CDATA[PowerPak menu editing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6105&amp;p=57353#p57353"><![CDATA[
My cousin has to use his NES and PowerPak with a half-broken TV. Each scanline is offset to the right by a random distance, much like the "fuzz out" in the second dose of <a href="http://www.pineight.com/tod/" class="postlink">Lockjaw: The Overdose</a>. The more black in the image, the more ragged the horizontal sync is. Depending on the amount of black, this could range from a 2-pixel range to an 8-pixel range. And guess how much black is in the PowerPak menu system.<br /><br />So would it be feasible to edit the PowerPak menu? He wants to do the following:<br /><ul><li>Turn on the monochrome bit or otherwise set the background to $00 gray (not $0F black) </li><li>Change the font to make the letters used in Game Genie codes more distinctive </li></ul><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Feb 28, 2010 4:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
